Name: Week 1: Build a Mascot Workshop
Description: For this round, imagine you're creating a new NFL team. Pick a theme song for this team, then in the comments tell us the team's name and mascot.

Name: Week 2: Waiver Wire
Description: Select a song that represents the gamble/hope/tension/strategy/#yolo of picking someone up from the waiver wire.

Name: Week 3: Teebow's Teebone
Description: What's the song Timmy Teebees lost his V card to (hint: it was likely Christian rock)

Name: Week 4: DRUG SCANDAL!!!
Description: A player just had massive drug scandal.  What song was he listening to when the cops busted down his door.  Be sure to include in your comment what kind of drugs he was using.

Name: Week 5: Stat Nerd
Description: Pick a song that caters to the analytic side of fantasy football.

Name: Week 6: Carrie Underwood Retires Unexpectedly
Description: Congrats football fans, Carrie Underwood has unexpectedly quit singing Sunday Night Football and you need to cast the next superstar.  Submit their audition tape.

Name: Week 7: Divorced from Reality
Description: What's the first song you play after your wife divorces you for watching too much football.

Name: Bye Week: Relax
Description: Submit the most relaxing song you can think of to bolster you through Bye Week. (Hint: think Yacht Rock)

Name: Week 9: Aaron Rodgers's Go-To Karaoke Song
Description: Arod's hittin the clurb and sangin the kay.  What's his go-to karaoke track?

Name: Week 10: Injury Blues
Description: Share a song that encapsulates the feeling when your star player is out with an injury.

Name: Week 11: Anthem for the Workin' Man
Description: Coors is casting their newest Superbowl commerical and they need you to come up with with the backing track for an ad campaign called "Anthem for the Workin' Man.‚Äù Suggest a lead role for their commercial in the comments.

Name: Week 12: Underdog Story
Description: Submit a song that embodies the spirit of a sleeper pick defying the odds.  If you're Ben Price or a Ben Price Doppleganger, tell us, in vivid detail, the actual Underdog Story.

Name: Week 13: Collegiate Memories
Description:
Submit a song whose title is a word or phrase found in lyrics of the Notre Dame Victory March: https://fightingirish.com/trads-nd-fightsong-html/

In the comments, tell us a story about something stupid you did in college while this song was playing (real or imagined).

Name: Week 14: Cut Out
Description: The pain! The agony!  Tell us what it feels like when you don't make the playoffs.

Name: Week 15: End Zone Dance
Description: Choose a song that you think would be perfect for an end zone touchdown celebration for winning this league and tell us what you learned about yourself in the process.
